Rowland said the woman lives in Oxford, a rural community of about 9800
people 30 miles southwest of Hartford. She was originally treated for
pneumonia and admitted Friday to the Derby hospital after being brought in
by a family member, said the hospital's president, Patrick Charmel.
[Five tests vs 3 tests; admitted into hospital on Wednesday and on Friday.
We await CDC's confirmation or denial of the Connecticut diagnosis. - Mod.MHJ
