[4
Date: November 20,2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNN [edited
<http://www.cnn.com/2001/HEALTH/conditions/11/20/senate.anthrax/index.html>

Further Washington contamination found
--------------------------------------
Meanwhile, trace amounts of anthrax were found in the offices of Sens. Ted
Kennedy, D-Massachusetts, and Christopher Dodd, D-Connecticut, both located
in the Russell building where the letter to Leahy was addressed.
Investigators believe these traces -- the first time the substance has been
found in the Russell building -- are the result of cross contamination with
a tainted letter. Dodd said the trace spores were found after testing in
the building last weekend.
